    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWe don't have luals/emmylua types for `:help event-data`. Currently we define ad hoc types e.g.: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/24684f90eac23a54d63c4d636ad0e6f2ddf3e9c4/runtime/lua/vim/ui.lua#L310-L315\n\nFor reference, we do define `vim.api.keyset.events` for the event *names*:  https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/24684f90eac23a54d63c4d636ad0e6f2ddf3e9c4/runtime/lua/vim/_meta/api_keysets.lua#L80-L82\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEnhance `src/nvim/auevents.lua` to specify event `data` types.\n\nDefine lua `@class` for each type. Name them something like `vim.event.bufadd.data`\n\nUpdate `src/gen/gen_vimdoc.lua` and `src/gen/gen_eval_files.lua` to generate docs and types.\n\n### Related\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34678\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/18750\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/19918",
